      "title": "Void Chicken",
      "pageid": 1891,
      "text": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div id=\"infoboxborder\">\n<table id=\"infoboxtable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" id=\"infoboxheader\">Void Chicken\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: center; padding-bottom: 5px;\"><img alt=\"Void Chicken.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/6/67/Void_Chicken.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"48\" height=\"48\" />\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" id=\"infoboxdetail\" style=\"text-align: center; font-style: italic;\">Well cared-for adult chickens lay eggs every day.  Lives in the coop.\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" id=\"infoboxsection\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Information\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td id=\"infoboxsection\">Building\n</td>\n<td id=\"infoboxdetail\"><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r120955\">.mw-parser-output .nametemplate{margin:2px 5px 1px 2px;display:block;white-space:nowrap}.mw-parser-output .nametemplateinline{margin:2px 0 1px 2px;display:inline;white-space:nowrap}.mw-parser-output .nametemplate img,.mw-parser-output .nametemplateinline img{max-width:none}</style><span class=\"nametemplate\"><img alt=\"Big Coop.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/d/d5/Big_Coop.png/24px-Big_Coop.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"28\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/d/d5/Big_Coop.png/36px-Big_Coop.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/thumb/d/d5/Big_Coop.png/48px-Big_Coop.png 2x\" /> <a href=\"/Coop\" title=\"Coop\">Big Coop</a></span>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td id=\"infoboxsection\">Purchase Price\n</td>\n<td id=\"infoboxdetail\">N/A\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td id=\"infoboxsection\">Produce\n</td>\n<td id=\"infoboxdetail\"><link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r120955\"/><span class=\"nametemplate\"><img alt=\"Void Egg.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/5/58/Void_Egg.png/24px-Void_Egg.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/5/58/Void_Egg.png/36px-Void_Egg.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/5/58/Void_Egg.png 2x\" /> <a href=\"/Void_Egg\" title=\"Void Egg\">Void Egg</a></span>\n</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p>The <b>Void Chicken</b> is an <a href=\"/Animals\" title=\"Animals\">animal</a> that lives in a <a href=\"/Coop\" title=\"Coop\">Big Coop</a>. Void Chickens can be hatched by placing a <a href=\"/Void_Egg\" title=\"Void Egg\">Void Egg</a> into an <a href=\"/Incubator\" title=\"Incubator\">Incubator</a>, taking <style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r120974\">.mw-parser-output .durationtemplate{margin:2px 5px 1px 2px;display:block;white-space:nowrap}.mw-parser-output .durationtemplateinline{margin:2px 0 1px 2px;display:inline;white-space:nowrap}.mw-parser-output .durationtemplate img,.mw-parser-output .durationtemplateinline img{max-width:none}</style><span class=\"durationtemplateinline\"><img alt=\"Time Icon.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/7/70/Time_Icon.png/24px-Time_Icon.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/7/70/Time_Icon.png/36px-Time_Icon.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/7/70/Time_Icon.png 2x\" /> 9,000m (5d 16h 40m)</span> to incubate, or <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r120974\"/><span class=\"durationtemplateinline\"><img alt=\"Time Icon.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/7/70/Time_Icon.png/24px-Time_Icon.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/7/70/Time_Icon.png/36px-Time_Icon.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/7/70/Time_Icon.png 2x\" /> 4,500m (2d 21h 40m)</span> with the <a href=\"/Farming#Farming_Skill\" title=\"Farming\">Coopmaster Profession</a>. There is no other way to obtain a Void Chicken.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Produce\">Produce</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/mediawiki/index.php?title=Void_Chicken&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Produce\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl><dd><i>Main article: <a href=\"/Animals#Produce\" title=\"Animals\">Animals#Produce</a></i></dd></dl>\n<p>Void Chickens who eat every day mature after 3 nights have passed. A mature and fed void chicken produces a <a href=\"/Void_Egg\" title=\"Void Egg\">Void Egg</a> every day, which can be placed in an <a href=\"/Incubator\" title=\"Incubator\">Incubator</a> to hatch another void chicken, or sold for <span style=\"display: none;\">data-sort-value=\"65\"&gt;</span><span class=\"no-wrap\"><img alt=\"Gold.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/18px-Gold.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/27px-Gold.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/36px-Gold.png 2x\" />65g</span>. The <a href=\"/Void_Egg\" title=\"Void Egg\">Void Egg</a> can be used in cooking recipes calling for an egg.\n</p><p>A Void Egg can be placed in the <a href=\"/Mayonnaise_Machine\" title=\"Mayonnaise Machine\">Mayonnaise Machine</a> to produce <a href=\"/Void_Mayonnaise\" title=\"Void Mayonnaise\">Void Mayonnaise</a>, which sells for <span style=\"display: none;\">data-sort-value=\"275\"&gt;</span><span class=\"no-wrap\"><img alt=\"Gold.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/18px-Gold.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/27px-Gold.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/36px-Gold.png 2x\" />275g</span>.\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable roundedborder\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Image\n</th>\n<th>Name\n</th>\n<th>Description\n</th>\n<th>Sell Price\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/File:Void_Egg.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Void Egg.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/5/58/Void_Egg.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"48\" height=\"48\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/Void_Egg\" title=\"Void Egg\">Void Egg</a>\n</td>\n<td>A jet-black egg with red flecks. It's warm to the touch.\n</td>\n<td><table class=\"no-wrap\" style=\"text-align: left; margin: 0; padding: 0; border-spacing: 0; border: 0;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n\t<td><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r146727\">.mw-parser-output .parent,.mw-parser-output .backimage,.mw-parser-output .backimagetransparent{position:relative;top:0;left:0}.mw-parser-output .backimage img,.mw-parser-output .foreimage img,.mw-parser-output .backimagetransparent img{display:block}.mw-parser-output .backimagetransparent img{opacity:0.6}.mw-parser-output .foreimage{position:absolute;bottom:0;right:0}</style><div class=\"parent\" style=\"width: 24px; height: auto; margin: 0 auto;\"><div class=\"backimage\"><img alt=\"Void Egg.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/5/58/Void_Egg.png/24px-Void_Egg.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/5/58/Void_Egg.png/36px-Void_Egg.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/5/58/Void_Egg.png 2x\" /></div><div class=\"foreimage\"></div></div></td>\n\t<td>65g\n\t</td>\n</tr><tr>\n\t<td><link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r146727\"/><div class=\"parent\" style=\"width: 24px; height: auto; margin: 0 auto;\"><div class=\"backimage\"><img alt=\"Void Egg.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/5/58/Void_Egg.png/24px-Void_Egg.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/5/58/Void_Egg.png/36px-Void_Egg.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/5/58/Void_Egg.png 2x\" /></div><div class=\"foreimage\"><img alt=\"Silver Quality Icon.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/8/8a/Silver_Quality_Icon.png/24px-Silver_Quality_Icon.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/8/8a/Silver_Quality_Icon.png/36px-Silver_Quality_Icon.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/8/8a/Silver_Quality_Icon.png 2x\" /></div></div></td>\n\t<td>81g\n\t</td>\n</tr><tr>\n\t<td><link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r146727\"/><div class=\"parent\" style=\"width: 24px; height: auto; margin: 0 auto;\"><div class=\"backimage\"><img alt=\"Void Egg.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/5/58/Void_Egg.png/24px-Void_Egg.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/5/58/Void_Egg.png/36px-Void_Egg.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/5/58/Void_Egg.png 2x\" /></div><div class=\"foreimage\"><img alt=\"Gold Quality Icon.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/4/47/Gold_Quality_Icon.png/24px-Gold_Quality_Icon.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/4/47/Gold_Quality_Icon.png/36px-Gold_Quality_Icon.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/4/47/Gold_Quality_Icon.png 2x\" /></div></div></td>\n\t<td>97g\n\t</td>\n</tr><tr>\n\t<td><link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r146727\"/><div class=\"parent\" style=\"width: 24px; height: auto; margin: 0 auto;\"><div class=\"backimage\"><img alt=\"Void Egg.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/5/58/Void_Egg.png/24px-Void_Egg.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/5/58/Void_Egg.png/36px-Void_Egg.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/5/58/Void_Egg.png 2x\" /></div><div class=\"foreimage\"><img alt=\"Iridium Quality Icon.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/e/e4/Iridium_Quality_Icon.png/24px-Iridium_Quality_Icon.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/e/e4/Iridium_Quality_Icon.png/36px-Iridium_Quality_Icon.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/e/e4/Iridium_Quality_Icon.png 2x\" /></div></div></td>\n\t<td>130g\n\t</td>\n</tr></tbody></table>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selling\">Selling</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/mediawiki/index.php?title=Void_Chicken&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Selling\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Void Chickens may be sold the same way as normal <a href=\"/Chicken\" title=\"Chicken\">chickens</a>. The more hearts the animal has, the higher its sell price. A new-born chick sells for <span style=\"display: none;\">data-sort-value=\"252\"&gt;</span><span class=\"no-wrap\"><img alt=\"Gold.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/18px-Gold.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/27px-Gold.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/36px-Gold.png 2x\" />252g</span>, and a maximum-heart Void Chicken for <span style=\"display: none;\">data-sort-value=\"1040\"&gt;</span><span class=\"no-wrap\"><img alt=\"Gold.png\" src=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/18px-Gold.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/27px-Gold.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/thumb/1/10/Gold.png/36px-Gold.png 2x\" />1,040g</span>, the same as for normal chickens.\n</p><p>To sell a coop or barn animal, right-click the animal after petting. The friendship/mood interface appears. Move the cursor over the gold coin button at the right to see how much you can sell the animal for. Click that button and the confirmation that follows to complete the sale.\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\" id=\"navbox\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"/Animals\" title=\"Animals\">Animals</a> and Produce\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th><a href=\"/Coop\" title=\"Coop\">Coop</a>\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/Chicken\" title=\"Chicken\">Chicken</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Egg\" title=\"Egg\">Egg</a> • <a href=\"/Large_Egg\" title=\"Large Egg\">Large Egg</a> • <a href=\"/Egg\" title=\"Egg\">Brown Egg</a> • <a href=\"/Large_Egg\" title=\"Large Egg\">Large Brown Egg</a>)</sup> • <a href=\"/Dinosaur\" title=\"Dinosaur\">Dinosaur</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Dinosaur_Egg\" title=\"Dinosaur Egg\">Dinosaur Egg</a>)</sup> • <a href=\"/Duck\" title=\"Duck\">Duck</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Duck_Egg\" title=\"Duck Egg\">Duck Egg</a> • <a href=\"/Duck_Feather\" title=\"Duck Feather\">Duck Feather</a>)</sup> • <a href=\"/Golden_Chicken\" title=\"Golden Chicken\">Golden Chicken</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Golden_Egg\" title=\"Golden Egg\">Golden Egg</a>)</sup> • <a href=\"/Rabbit\" title=\"Rabbit\">Rabbit</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Wool\" title=\"Wool\">Wool</a> • <a href=\"/Rabbit%27s_Foot\" title=\"Rabbit&#39;s Foot\">Rabbit's Foot</a>)</sup> • <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Void Chicken</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Void_Egg\" title=\"Void Egg\">Void Egg</a>)</sup>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th><a href=\"/Barn\" title=\"Barn\">Barn</a>\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/Cow\" title=\"Cow\">Cow</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Milk\" title=\"Milk\">Milk</a> • <a href=\"/Large_Milk\" title=\"Large Milk\">Large Milk</a>)</sup> • <a href=\"/Goat\" title=\"Goat\">Goat</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Goat_Milk\" title=\"Goat Milk\">Goat Milk</a> • <a href=\"/Large_Goat_Milk\" title=\"Large Goat Milk\">Large Goat Milk</a>)</sup> • <a href=\"/Sheep\" title=\"Sheep\">Sheep</a>  <sup>(<a href=\"/Wool\" title=\"Wool\">Wool</a>)</sup> • <a href=\"/Ostrich\" title=\"Ostrich\">Ostrich</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Ostrich_Egg\" title=\"Ostrich Egg\">Ostrich Egg</a>)</sup> • <a href=\"/Pig\" title=\"Pig\">Pig</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Truffle\" title=\"Truffle\">Truffle</a>)</sup>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th><a href=\"/Fish_Pond\" title=\"Fish Pond\">Fish Pond</a>\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/Fish\" title=\"Fish\">Fish</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Roe\" title=\"Roe\">Roe</a>)</sup>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"no-wrap\"><a href=\"/Slime_Hutch\" title=\"Slime Hutch\">Slime Hutch</a>\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/Slimes\" title=\"Slimes\">Slimes</a> <sup>(<a href=\"/Slime\" title=\"Slime\">Slime</a> • <a href=\"/Slime_Ball\" title=\"Slime Ball\">Slime Ball</a> • <a href=\"/Slime_Egg\" title=\"Slime Egg\">Slime Egg</a>)</sup>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Other\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/Animals#Cat_or_Dog\" title=\"Animals\">Cat</a> • <a href=\"/Animals#Cat_or_Dog\" title=\"Animals\">Dog</a> • <a href=\"/Animals#Horse\" title=\"Animals\">Horse</a> • <a href=\"/Animals#Additional_Pets\" title=\"Animals\">Turtle</a>\n</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260413162739\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.119 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.151 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 2654/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 9667/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 890/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 10/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 3424/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.005/7.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 582 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  100.885      1 -total\n 45.10%   45.495      1 Template:Infobox_animal\n 30.17%   30.442      1 Template:Qualityprice\n 29.37%   29.628      2 Template:Description\n 12.50%   12.607      2 Template:Name\n  9.72%    9.809      4 Template:Overlayimg\n  7.27%    7.336      2 Template:Duration\n  4.97%    5.011      4 Template:Price\n  4.65%    4.694      1 Template:Main_article\n  2.37%    2.391      1 Template:InfoboxSEO\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:1891-0!canonical and timestamp 20260413162739 and revision id 182306\n -->\n</div>",
      "wikitext": "{{Infobox animal\n|image    = Void Chicken.png\n|building = {{name|Big Coop}}\n|produce  = {{name|Void Egg}}\n}}\nThe '''Void Chicken''' is an [[Animals|animal]] that lives in a [[Coop|Big Coop]]. Void Chickens can be hatched by placing a [[Void Egg]] into an [[Incubator]], taking {{duration|9,000m (5d 16h 40m)|class=inline}} to incubate, or {{duration|4,500m (2d 21h 40m)|class=inline}} with the [[Farming#Farming Skill|Coopmaster Profession]]. There is no other way to obtain a Void Chicken.\n\n==Produce==\n{{main article|Animals#Produce}}\nVoid Chickens who eat every day mature after 3 nights have passed. A mature and fed void chicken produces a [[Void Egg]] every day, which can be placed in an [[Incubator]] to hatch another void chicken, or sold for {{Price|65}}. The [[Void Egg]] can be used in cooking recipes calling for an egg.\n\nA Void Egg can be placed in the [[Mayonnaise Machine]] to produce [[Void Mayonnaise]], which sells for {{Price|275}}.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable roundedborder\"\n!Image\n!Name\n!Description\n!Sell Price\n|-\n|[[File:Void Egg.png]]\n|[[Void Egg]]\n|{{Description|Void Egg}}\n|{{Qualityprice|Void Egg|65|dsv=false}}\n|}\n\n==Selling==\nVoid Chickens may be sold the same way as normal [[chicken]]s. The more hearts the animal has, the higher its sell price. A new-born chick sells for {{Price|252}}, and a maximum-heart Void Chicken for {{Price|1040}}, the same as for normal chickens.\n\nTo sell a coop or barn animal, right-click the animal after petting. The friendship/mood interface appears. Move the cursor over the gold coin button at the right to see how much you can sell the animal for. Click that button and the confirmation that follows to complete the sale.\n\n{{NavboxAnimals}}\n\n[[Category:Coop animals]]\n\n[[de:Schattenhuhn]]\n[[es:Gallina sombría]]\n[[fr:Poulet vide]]\n[[it:Gallina del vuoto]]\n[[ja:闇ニワトリ]]\n[[ko:공허 닭]]\n[[hu:Űr csirke]]\n[[pt:Galinha nula]]\n[[ru:Курица пустоты]]\n[[tr:Boşluk Tavuğu]]\n[[zh:虚空鸡]]"
